text: Holmes–Dakin Building is a historic commercial building located at Hannibal, Marion County, Missouri. It was built in 1894, and is a two-story brick structure with a coursed rubble foundation and a flat roof. It features a corbelled brick frieze with matching corbelled parapet, capped by a stone molding. It originally housed a cigar factory. and Site map It was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1986. ==References== Category:Commercial buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Commercial buildings completed in 1894 Category:Buildings and structures in Hannibal, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Marion County, Missouri
